HEADWORD: Cangue
<hw>Cangue</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>cang</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[F. <ets>cangue</ets>, fr. Pg.
<ets>canga</ets> yoke.]</ety> <def>A very broad and heavy wooden collar
which certain offenders in China are compelled to wear as a
punishment.</def>⟦br⟧
